title.narrative: PEACEBUILDING AND SURVIVE AND THRIVE- PROTECTION FROM CONFLICT AND DISASTERS

description.narrative: Strengthened capacities of health authorities and local government units to scale up quality maternal, neonatal, child and adolescent health, nutrition, water and sanitation services and information in BARMM, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, more children, adolescents and women, particularly the most vulnerable, benefit from improved and equitable neonatal, child, maternal and adolescent health and nutrition services, and adopt healthy life practices.

description.narrative: Progress towards ZOD;accelerated with an additional 314 communities and 26 municipalities verified as OD-free during the year. 78% of communities and 58% of municipalities in Maguindanao province;are;ZOD certified. Maguindanao province is on track to become free of OD in 2022.; Progress towards COVID-19 prevention was mixed with over 5 million people receiving information on prevention, and community-based nutrition and vaccination services to underserved areas restarted in 17 municipalities after stalling last year due to impacts of COVID-19.;COVID-19 vaccination coverage in BARMM remains the lowest in the country, and a more intensive effort to achieve high coverage required in 2022.;;; | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:23/12/2021
